msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/transform/bend.rst:36
msgid "The amount of rotation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/transform/bend.rst:37
msgid "Radius"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/transform/bend.rst:38
msgid "The sharpness of the bend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/transform/bend.rst:45
msgid "Clamp"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/transform/bend.rst:40
msgid ""
"Normally the arc turns through a clamped rotation angle with the selected"
" elements extended along a tangent line beyond that (see above left). "
"When the clamp is deactivated, the arc continues around aligning the "
"selected elements into a circle (right)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/transform/bend.rst:44
msgid ""
"When off :kbd:`Alt` all selected elements follow a circle, even when "
"outside the segment between the 3D cursor and the mouse."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/transform/bend.rst:49
msgid ""
"Unlike most other transform modes *Bend* is not effected by *Pivot Point*"
" or *Transform Orientation*, always using the View Plane instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/transform/bend.rst:54
msgid ""
"You can turn the bend angle through multiple rotations potentially "
"forming a spiral shape."
msgstr ""

